
Run Time Polymorphism Keyword: Polymorphism ise nables us to invoke derirved class methods using a base class reference variables at run time.
Virtual keyword indicated, the method can be overridden in any derived class.
late binding and dynamic binding.
==============

Definition: 
-----------



Usage in Code:
--------------


Example:
--------
public class A
    {
        public virtual void Print()
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Base Class");
        }
    }

    public class B : A
    {
        public new void Print()
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Dervice Class");
        }
    }
    
    Method Hiding
    example1: using new keyword in dervice class
    example2:  B a = new B();
              ((A)a).Print();

